# LF everywhere: in the index, in the working tree, on every machine.
#
# `core.autocrlf=input` normalises on the way IN, so commits are already LF, but
# it leaves whatever the working tree happens to hold. A tool that writes CRLF
# then produces a file that lints red locally and clean in CI, which is a
# confusing way to lose an afternoon. `eol=lf` settles it on checkout too, and
# it applies to anyone who clones, whatever their global config says.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries git must not touch.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.ttf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.pdf binary
